Put Credit Spread Backtests

September 2016 - Present

Warning

The backtester is not perfect! Many previously identified bugs have been found that resulted in unexpected returns. All known bugs are fixed, but there may be others remaining. Before you take on any trade, study the backtest and simulated trades thoroughly to ensure accuracy.

Backtest data is for general information purposes only. Past performance may not be indicative of future results.

FILLS

All backtest fills are $0.02 worse than the mid price at both entry and exit. I have compared my actual fills against backtest fills very closely and have adjusted backtest fills to as closely mimic my actual fills as possible. My actual fills are made by an autotrader, and while you might think a computer can get better fills than a human, I don't think that's the case. With a little extra effort/focus, I think you'll get these fills or better if you are manually trading.

CLOSING TRADES

When spreads are bought to close in these backtests, only the short strike is closed. The long strike remains open until expiration. This was done, because in most cases, there isn't enough liquidity in the long strike to close it once your spread has decayed 70%+

FEES

Brokerage fees are calculated at $1 per contract, and all returns are after fees. No assignment fees are included.

If you notice any incorrect data or missing/broken links, please send me a message or hop in our Discord server
